In Esitjeni, we can observe on a smaller scale the ills that plague Swaziland: the highest rate of HIV infection and the lowest life expectancy in the world, according to UNICEF.
The population practically never accepts male circumcision, a measure that nevertheless guarantees a proven reduction in the risk of infection by half.
