The hearing is expected to resume this weekend, with prosecutors expected to argue that conditions of detention were warranted.
The Pentagon has confirmed that Manning has been jailed in accordance with the regulations governing the conditions of detention of all detainees at Quantico.
The charges against Manning include the theft of public property or documents, collusion with the enemy, leading to the illegal publication of information on the Internet, and the transmission of information relating to national defense.
