Although the rocket fire from Gaza has killed about 30 Israelis since 2004, Israel has been spared from suicide bombings, including thanks to the separation barrier that encroaches on the West Bank, the main piece of what could be a Palestinian state, and which protects Jewish settlements that continue to fall into international disrepair.
