Police services have stopped charging adults 21 and older with minor marijuana possession, as the law will come into force in the coming weeks.
But prosecutors in Colorado’s more conservative ridings have called for speeding up existing marijuana cases and continue to charge people who own them.
At the same time, several cities from the suburbs of Denver to the western mountains are currently voting to prevent the opening of state-approved marijuana sales stores in their neighborhoods.
