At the moment, this judgment is not respected.
This is a problem between a South American country and a Central American country.
Conflicts are inevitable, but they must be overcome by the will to move forward together.
We need to solve them as a whole to overcome them and move forward.
At the same time, he expressed confidence in the sound resolution of the maritime border dispute between Peru and Chile in the same court and said it is "beneficial for Latin America to seize international forums if the two countries agree to accept a judgment as firm as it is".
Referring to the possibility of his nomination as a candidate for the upcoming presidential elections in Ecuador, in order to fight for a third consecutive term, he noted that he saw this possibility "with a lot of optimism and joy, although sometimes it is quite difficult".
